WEBVTT

00:05.100 --> 00:06.446
Everybody dies.

00:06.861 --> 00:08.105
That's just the way it is.

00:09.443 --> 00:11.990
I'm told I'm not supposed
to argue or question

00:12.073 --> 00:14.161
or even try to understand.

00:14.796 --> 00:16.579
I'm told a lot these days.

00:17.131 --> 00:20.183
Ever since my life was
snuffed out by a toilet seat

00:20.234 --> 00:22.712
and I joined the ranks of the undead.

00:22.958 --> 00:25.068
You, little dead girl,
are gonna be a grim reaper.

00:25.703 --> 00:27.494
My name is George Lass.

00:28.328 --> 00:29.717
I take souls for a living.

00:30.867 --> 00:32.003
This is Rube.

00:32.198 --> 00:33.239
He's undead too.

00:33.879 --> 00:37.125
He's the one who gets the list,
who's to die, when and where,

00:37.319 --> 00:40.103
which he passes on to the
rest of us grim reapers.

00:40.274 --> 00:42.859
- E.T.D. ?
- Estimated Time of Death.

00:43.899 --> 00:46.009
Do you guys get off
dropping pianos on people ?

00:46.091 --> 00:48.676
It's not our job to drop the
pianos or the toilet seats.

00:48.911 --> 00:51.245
- Whose job is it ?
- Gravelings.

00:53.207 --> 00:55.020
Reapers don't get a free ride.

00:55.454 --> 00:56.376
What are you doing ?

00:56.514 --> 00:57.543
Collecting my salary.

00:57.620 --> 01:00.811
We don't get paid like
through proper channels.

01:00.871 --> 01:04.933
- Hi, I'm Dolores Herbig as in...
- Her big brown eyes.

01:05.013 --> 01:09.397
What kind of universe would give me the
power to extract souls from people's bodies

01:09.474 --> 01:12.945
but still force me to keep a
suck-ass job if I wanna eat.

01:14.235 --> 01:15.357
This was my home.

01:15.745 --> 01:17.122
And this was my family.

01:17.677 --> 01:19.130
They're having trouble copping.

01:19.533 --> 01:21.536
Keeping a dead animal in your toy box.

01:21.623 --> 01:23.515
It's something a crazy person would do.

01:23.811 --> 01:24.865
I'm not crazy.

01:25.489 --> 01:27.659
I was having trouble copping too.

01:28.012 --> 01:30.097
I don't think I'm
supposed to be doing this.

01:30.615 --> 01:31.600
You're learning.

01:31.641 --> 01:33.471
You gotta think about all
the things you like and

01:33.528 --> 01:35.468
decide if they're worth
sticking around for.

01:36.713 --> 01:37.808
And if they are...

01:37.971 --> 01:39.344
you'll find a way to do this.

01:39.743 --> 01:40.704
What if I don't ?

01:41.254 --> 01:42.240
Then you go away.

