02:52.182 --> 02:53.173
When I was alive,

02:53.308 --> 02:56.274
I never looked at the
obituaries, like, not even once.

02:57.163 --> 02:58.735
Now I read them first.

02:58.966 --> 03:00.692
The reaper's sport pages.

03:01.113 --> 03:03.738
And every time I see
someone who lived to even 50,

03:04.014 --> 03:05.315
it kind of annoys me.

03:06.918 --> 03:08.490
Was your name ever in the paper ?

03:09.503 --> 03:10.495
Constantly.

03:10.932 --> 03:12.188
I still have all the clipping.

03:12.226 --> 03:14.524
I made the police reports
a couple of times, you know,

03:14.552 --> 03:18.315
unidentified male slender built seen
fleeing the premises, that kind of things.

03:18.592 --> 03:19.733
That doesn't count.

03:20.045 --> 03:21.659
What about you, sweetie ?

03:22.432 --> 03:23.432
Do tell.

03:23.946 --> 03:26.670
Teen killed by falling
debris from space station.

03:27.418 --> 03:30.178
Technically, that was
the day after your life.

03:30.280 --> 03:34.365
My demise went unreported. Drug related
deaths in the 60s were very common.

03:35.432 --> 03:36.454
I've gotta go wee-wee.

03:40.306 --> 03:41.504
Was your death reported ?

03:41.653 --> 03:44.980
Oh please ! I perished in a huge
fire in the set of Gone with the Wind.

03:45.312 --> 03:46.284
Not a word, huh ?

03:46.378 --> 03:47.964
Nothing. The story was buried.

03:48.681 --> 03:50.505
- And three days later...
- So were you.

03:50.541 --> 03:52.819
But my picture was in the
paper a whole lot before I died.

03:52.820 --> 03:53.498
Why ?

03:53.499 --> 03:56.504
On the arm of whatever famous
man I was sleeping with.

03:57.694 --> 03:59.096
Right. Not my thing.

03:59.650 --> 04:01.380
- You never slept with anybody ?
- No.

04:01.902 --> 04:02.824
Why didn't you ?

04:03.012 --> 04:06.357
Well, Daisy, first of
all, I was 18 years old.

04:06.608 --> 04:08.835
- Not a good excuse.
- I never had a boyfriend.

04:09.111 --> 04:11.000
- Not really a problem.
- I lived at home

04:11.127 --> 04:12.882
with my parents and my little sister.

04:13.073 --> 04:14.608
Never heard of a car ?

04:16.095 --> 04:17.764
Is it just my imagination or

04:17.969 --> 04:20.743
have I become much more attractive
since I've laid of the booze

04:20.793 --> 04:22.172
and, you know, whatnot.

04:22.366 --> 04:23.369
Your breath is better.

04:23.626 --> 04:24.910
Your eyes are less puffy.

04:25.060 --> 04:27.747
You don't have as much
drool around your mouth

04:27.840 --> 04:28.776
which is nice.

04:28.777 --> 04:31.946
Yet the most attractive thing about
when you were drinking and whatnot

04:32.002 --> 04:34.752
is that you really had no
idea if you were attractive.

04:34.926 --> 04:36.776
Because when people
know they're attractive,

04:36.958 --> 04:37.870
they're not.

04:37.916 --> 04:40.245
And it's not about
what's on the outside.

04:40.445 --> 04:44.398
It's not about this, it's
about this. It's about here.

04:45.532 --> 04:48.523
Then he's a very handsome man.

04:52.847 --> 04:53.902
But am I pretty ?

04:53.944 --> 04:55.842
Oh you're a darling, you
make my heart flutter.

04:55.917 --> 04:56.912
Mine too.

04:57.014 --> 04:58.364
- Really ?
- No.

04:58.668 --> 05:00.470
There are souls to be taken, folks.

05:00.532 --> 05:02.094
This morning before breakfast.

05:02.247 --> 05:03.171
One, two.

05:03.625 --> 05:04.582
Three.

05:05.974 --> 05:07.112
Four, five.

05:07.628 --> 05:08.877
Why do I only get one ?

05:09.133 --> 05:10.782
Because three doesn't
add to five evenly.

05:11.289 --> 05:12.257
What does Roxy get ?

05:12.584 --> 05:13.529
Huh, usually...

05:14.258 --> 05:15.957
Eggs. Side of fruit.

05:16.103 --> 05:18.227
I was thinking hash browns today.

05:18.708 --> 05:19.681
Nice.

05:19.988 --> 05:23.444
These are all at the farmer's
market in exactly 27 minutes.

05:23.515 --> 05:24.590
I smell a disaster.

05:25.568 --> 05:27.689
No, 5 deaths is not a disaster.

05:27.822 --> 05:29.418
How many deaths is a disaster ?

05:29.633 --> 05:31.251
More than five. Five is bullshit.

05:31.369 --> 05:34.007
- How many ?
- 16 to 20: disaster.

05:34.381 --> 05:36.362
21 and up: catastrophe.

05:36.464 --> 05:38.405
8 to 15, it's a calamity.

05:38.477 --> 05:40.161
- 7 and under ?
- That's a crying shame.

05:40.361 --> 05:42.291
Pick me up some tomatoes
while you're up there.

05:42.413 --> 05:43.323
Sure.

05:43.811 --> 05:45.281
- See you later.
- Goodbye.

05:50.994 --> 05:53.729
- Anything in the paper ?
- Two heart attacks and a stroke.

05:55.066 --> 05:56.000
Nice.

05:57.461 --> 06:00.758
Trying to find your reap is kinda
like a game of hide and go seek.

06:01.005 --> 06:02.428
Except that when I find you,

06:02.663 --> 06:05.311
when I put the tag on
you, you're out for good.

06:05.879 --> 06:07.978
Ready or not, you're dead.

06:09.894 --> 06:13.953
Okay, enough with the game. I haven't
had breakfast and momma wants a waffle.

06:14.296 --> 06:16.309
Come out ! Come out ! Wherever you are.

06:17.450 --> 06:19.022
Oh we have a winner.

06:19.320 --> 06:20.272
Thanks boys !

06:21.085 --> 06:22.139
This has been a treat.

06:25.474 --> 06:27.275
I'm done. Two of the hard hats get it.

06:27.604 --> 06:28.588
Wanna get a latté ?

06:29.088 --> 06:31.895
No, you gotta go. I've
got something to do.

06:33.865 --> 06:35.458
It's been two hours now, guys.

06:35.540 --> 06:36.952
I still smell propane.

06:37.316 --> 06:38.766
This is killing my business.

06:42.519 --> 06:44.029
I'm usually swamped by nine.

06:44.428 --> 06:46.711
Today, you're tow up by ten.

06:47.153 --> 06:49.620
You think Eliza Doolittle had
to put up with this nonsense ?

06:49.804 --> 06:51.627
- Who ?
- Audrey Hepburn, sweetheart.

06:51.842 --> 06:54.321
Look at me. Still
waiting for Rex Harrison.

06:54.357 --> 06:55.681
Don't hold your fucking breath.

06:55.758 --> 06:58.151
You see this is who I sell flowers to.

06:58.329 --> 07:03.398
Men who need to apologize for
the things they say to women.

07:03.633 --> 07:05.604
And who end up paying
for it one way or another.

07:10.582 --> 07:11.501
Pink lilies.

07:14.282 --> 07:15.204
On the house.

07:15.773 --> 07:17.344
My first customer of the day.

07:18.446 --> 07:21.277
Oh great! She can see the
guilt written all over me.

07:22.440 --> 07:23.459
Mine too.

07:31.476 --> 07:32.464
I couldn't find it.

07:32.504 --> 07:34.753
Geez ! You people can find Pearl
Harbour in the middle of the night

07:34.830 --> 07:36.299
but you can't find a gas link!

07:36.780 --> 07:38.481
I'm Chinese, cocksucker !

07:45.039 --> 07:47.573
Gravelings... fucking troublemakers.

08:03.097 --> 08:04.337
Bodies everywhere.

08:06.830 --> 08:08.673
And a dead flower girl in the middle.

08:10.449 --> 08:12.462
It was like a really fucked up wedding.

08:15.524 --> 08:17.166
She gave me a pretty flower.

08:17.684 --> 08:18.770
And what did I give her ?

08:19.502 --> 08:20.457
Nothing.

08:20.716 --> 08:21.771
I took her soul.

08:22.590 --> 08:24.985
I don't know why but I felt
like I had betrayed her.

08:26.040 --> 08:26.993
Somehow.

08:32.784 --> 08:35.666
The last time I had seen a
death like this was my own.

08:36.982 --> 08:39.448
And I wanted to run
away as fast as I could.

08:45.072 --> 08:46.017
Order up !

08:48.842 --> 08:51.057
You know what's best about being sober ?

08:52.430 --> 08:54.493
Not waking up in a
pool of your own vomit ?

08:54.892 --> 08:55.917
Definitely that, yeah.

08:56.372 --> 08:57.908
But no, it's the taste of food.

08:59.888 --> 09:01.503
I mean, after all these years,

09:01.569 --> 09:04.319
I've finally realized
why you guys eat here.

09:04.456 --> 09:06.049
In da fucking Waffle House.

09:06.714 --> 09:07.755
This is a wise move.

09:08.769 --> 09:11.041
Bacchus has drown many
more men than Neptune.

09:11.558 --> 09:12.500
Bacchus ?

09:13.198 --> 09:15.593
He's the Greek god of "why
don't you read a fucking book?"

09:16.156 --> 09:18.461
When did you die ?
Nineteen sixty something ?

09:18.942 --> 09:19.960
66.

09:20.519 --> 09:25.459
Taking every nasty ass drug you could
get your nasty ass pause on for 40 years.

09:25.536 --> 09:26.524
Yeah.

09:26.525 --> 09:27.825
Oh no, no, not everything.

09:27.871 --> 09:29.488
'Cause I was definitely
afraid of needles.

09:29.537 --> 09:30.759
And I still am.

09:30.969 --> 09:33.569
They've made great strides
in the design of needles.

09:34.358 --> 09:35.281
They're sharper.

09:35.398 --> 09:37.806
- Sharper ?
- Sharper is less painful.

09:39.924 --> 09:41.552
Are you gonna finish those hash browns ?

09:41.992 --> 09:42.930
Probably not.

09:46.478 --> 09:48.148
Fucking bloody hell !

09:49.125 --> 09:50.044
I'm outta here.

09:52.294 --> 09:53.272
Did you see that ?

09:54.450 --> 09:56.656
I mean because I wanted
some of her hash browns...

09:57.681 --> 09:58.555
I was there.

09:58.556 --> 10:01.013
I have never seen such violence
over such small potatoes.

10:01.494 --> 10:02.667
Well, that was almost clever.

10:02.796 --> 10:03.994
What was almost clever, Rube ?

10:04.081 --> 10:05.899
Thinking hash browns are small potatoes.

10:06.426 --> 10:07.368
I don't get it.

10:07.726 --> 10:09.631
Because hash browns are small potatoes.

10:10.029 --> 10:10.945
Never mind.

10:13.610 --> 10:14.949
- Daisy.
- Roxy.

10:15.217 --> 10:16.737
This weather kinda suits you.

10:17.136 --> 10:19.021
You know, Roxy, I really
don't think it does.

10:19.830 --> 10:20.854
Off to work you go.

10:22.646 --> 10:24.065
Why do I even bother with you ?

10:24.461 --> 10:27.224
Because I'm one of the
few fools who gets you.

10:27.480 --> 10:29.476
Really ? What do you get ?

10:29.834 --> 10:31.999
When I go to the pound to pick up a dog,

10:32.169 --> 10:34.089
I don't take the one that wags his tail

10:34.172 --> 10:36.582
and licks my face and jumps all over me.

10:36.793 --> 10:38.118
I pick the one in the corner.

10:38.292 --> 10:40.183
Alone. Shaky.

10:40.767 --> 10:43.214
Well, go on. Get inside
where it's warm. go girl !

10:43.341 --> 10:45.116
- Okay.
- Here you go.

10:45.333 --> 10:46.833
Daisy Adair...

10:47.780 --> 10:48.779
Chihuahua.

10:50.034 --> 10:53.654
Hello ! Is anyone here ?

10:55.978 --> 10:56.943
Reggie ?

11:02.128 --> 11:02.900
You know...

11:02.901 --> 11:04.139
when someone calls your name,

11:04.340 --> 11:07.119
you could say "Hi! I'm
here ! What's up mom ?"

11:07.631 --> 11:09.971
A simple "What is it ?" would suffice.

11:10.267 --> 11:11.193
What is it ?

11:13.550 --> 11:15.634
This is how you're gonna
spend your school holiday ?

11:16.033 --> 11:16.984
Looks that way.

11:17.232 --> 11:19.633
I just saw Bridget and Annie
heading down to the park.

11:19.663 --> 11:21.033
Why don't you go catch up with them ?

11:21.149 --> 11:22.089
I don't think so.

11:22.234 --> 11:23.452
Give me one good reason.

11:23.637 --> 11:25.594
I don't really like
getting baked before noon.

11:25.818 --> 11:26.768
Baked ?

11:29.004 --> 11:29.950
Oh...

11:31.670 --> 11:35.934
- Reggie, I'm not going to...
- I haven't. I won't.

11:36.087 --> 11:38.577
Did you ever catch your
sister doing stuff ?

11:38.797 --> 11:40.564
No. Did you ?

11:40.778 --> 11:44.020
No. Never. I don't think
your sister smoked pot.

11:44.117 --> 11:45.387
I searched constantly.

11:46.626 --> 11:48.311
All what Georgia ever did was...

11:49.729 --> 11:51.418
pretty much what you're doing right now.

11:52.217 --> 11:53.154
Whatever.

11:53.455 --> 11:54.449
Mom.

11:54.494 --> 11:56.665
Your father and I have
another doctor's appointment.

11:56.723 --> 11:58.207
Stay out of the park.

11:59.262 --> 12:01.935
I better not see any cherry
stains on those cushions.

12:03.815 --> 12:05.223
It's not a real doctor.

12:05.861 --> 12:06.782
It's a shrink.

12:12.996 --> 12:15.390
Rube didn't want me
lurking around my old house.

12:15.717 --> 12:17.495
He didn't want me spying on my family.

12:18.109 --> 12:21.027
He says that a reaper should
be like a soldier in a foxhole.

12:21.708 --> 12:23.101
Lay low, don't be a hero,

12:23.419 --> 12:25.384
don't take any unnecessary risk.

12:25.911 --> 12:29.029
What's the point of keeping your head
down once it's already been blown off ?

12:31.675 --> 12:32.969
How did it go this morning ?

12:33.013 --> 12:35.901
Ah ! Real fun ! Try to get me
another one like that real soon.

12:35.984 --> 12:36.950
How about a breakfast ?

12:37.115 --> 12:40.278
I'll have the Johnny Vegas over
easy and a small grapefruit juice.

12:40.374 --> 12:42.513
You could hear the explosion
all the way over here.

12:42.603 --> 12:44.405
The Johnny Vegas comes with a side.

12:44.492 --> 12:45.609
That was disgusting.

12:45.726 --> 12:49.060
Her body was blown to pieces.

12:49.171 --> 12:52.571
Her brain was... cottage cheese.

12:55.483 --> 12:56.627
Pretty flower.

12:56.960 --> 12:59.028
- Did someone betray you ?
- What ?

12:59.208 --> 13:00.958
Did some guy screw you over ?

13:01.063 --> 13:04.382
I thought we had decided that you
and romantic entanglements were...

13:04.656 --> 13:05.613
It's not a good idea.

13:05.767 --> 13:07.139
And I thought George was a virgin.

13:07.339 --> 13:10.012
What? No! No guy.

13:10.134 --> 13:12.371
And who told you I was a
virgin, did you tell him that ?

13:12.582 --> 13:13.590
- No.
- Yes, she did.

13:13.703 --> 13:15.162
It's just a flower. Fuck !

13:15.879 --> 13:17.984
I only got flowers when
somebody betrayed me.

13:18.177 --> 13:19.401
I didn't betray anyone.

13:19.581 --> 13:20.564
Sure didn't say you did.

13:21.543 --> 13:22.919
It takes like ass.

13:23.052 --> 13:23.982
Try that.

13:24.127 --> 13:27.297
I'm trying to stay off the
ice juice but thank you.

13:27.604 --> 13:30.444
You know who sent beautiful
flowers, French tulips ?

13:30.707 --> 13:33.246
I'll just give you his
initials Douglas Fairbanks Jr.

13:33.696 --> 13:36.512
Errol Flynn, all that
money... Carnations.

13:36.758 --> 13:41.480
Cannot sit here and listen to more
witless stories about star fucking.

13:42.709 --> 13:43.610
You and you.

13:43.927 --> 13:44.881
Let's go.

13:44.899 --> 13:45.865
Rube ! Sorry.

13:45.944 --> 13:47.752
But I've got to finish Roxy's breakfast.

13:48.084 --> 13:50.091
Here. Why don't you take it to go ?

13:50.208 --> 13:52.333
It's a disgusting habit,
eating off someone's plate.

13:52.400 --> 13:54.649
You wanna be an ex-drug addict ?

13:54.694 --> 13:56.410
Why don't you behave like one, huh ?

13:57.237 --> 13:58.984
Crazy fucking fuck !

13:59.318 --> 14:03.138
How I wish the words would roll
out my tongue as they do yours!

14:10.925 --> 14:12.040
Another outdoor death !

14:12.097 --> 14:13.859
My lips are getting so chapped.

14:14.038 --> 14:16.085
Roxy says I look like a dog.

14:16.347 --> 14:17.586
I didn't betray him.

14:17.659 --> 14:20.202
Do I look like some kind of
stray that needs to be saved ?

14:20.263 --> 14:22.634
I'm really pretty, don't you think ?

14:23.686 --> 14:25.296
I need verbal reassurance.

14:25.728 --> 14:26.699
You're not a dog.

14:27.145 --> 14:29.408
- Say the thing.
- You're really pretty.

14:29.500 --> 14:30.647
Say the whole thing !

14:30.995 --> 14:33.791
You're the most exquisite
beauty the world has ever seen.

14:34.614 --> 14:35.553
I gotta go.

14:35.862 --> 14:37.302
What about your breakfast ?

14:37.442 --> 14:38.392
I don't want it.

14:40.954 --> 14:41.942
Forgot your flower.

14:42.555 --> 14:43.535
I don't want it.

14:46.730 --> 14:47.702
I did want it.

14:48.186 --> 14:50.692
I just didn't feel like
carrying around the reminder

14:50.755 --> 14:52.919
of my morning death the rest of my day.

15:00.185 --> 15:01.106
Hi, Crystal!

15:01.571 --> 15:04.566
Which is why it wasn't so
bad walking into Happy Time.

15:04.966 --> 15:08.381
Where the only thing ever written
on a post-it note was stuff like...

15:08.776 --> 15:09.806
"Who farted ?"

15:10.010 --> 15:12.336
and "Ten copies A.S.A.P."

15:12.417 --> 15:14.521
and "Please see me."

15:25.334 --> 15:26.309
Oh Millie !

15:26.681 --> 15:28.359
- Dolores ?
- I got news.

15:29.174 --> 15:33.179
Bad news. I have to
hire my boss' nephew.

15:33.348 --> 15:35.574
I'm sorry, Millie,
but this boy, Brennan,

15:35.625 --> 15:37.516
has had a world of
trouble finding a job.

15:37.643 --> 15:39.275
You're firing me ?

15:39.389 --> 15:41.299
You're shitcanning me just like that ?

15:41.376 --> 15:43.873
No ! Why would you think that ?

15:44.299 --> 15:47.463
Bad news, boss' nephew.

15:48.068 --> 15:49.408
Seemed where you were headed.

15:49.454 --> 15:51.708
I want you to train him, Millie.

15:51.872 --> 15:53.545
And I don't care for the language.

15:53.771 --> 15:55.502
Although I do kind of like that phrase.

15:55.624 --> 15:57.049
Shitcan... Shitcan...

15:57.113 --> 15:59.054
That's the bad news ? I
have to train someone ?

15:59.151 --> 16:01.866
