33:25.317 --> 33:29.609
and I just don't like to see your
talent wasted on projects like Brennan.

33:29.692 --> 33:31.007
What are we talking about ?

33:31.072 --> 33:33.659
We're talking about a
promotion, you silly goose.

33:34.099 --> 33:35.061
We are ?

33:35.062 --> 33:36.081
Oh I think we are.

33:36.193 --> 33:40.146
Two more days a week and two
hundred dollars more a week.

33:40.489 --> 33:41.447
You're shitting me ?

33:41.534 --> 33:43.802
Your new position at
Happy Time will be to, huh,

33:44.135 --> 33:45.948
interview potential temps.

33:46.040 --> 33:48.702
We're frittering away
your talents at data entry.

33:48.897 --> 33:52.306
And training boys like Brennan,
that's a waste of your time.

33:52.772 --> 33:54.212
Do we understand each other ?

33:55.282 --> 33:56.782
I won't let you down.

34:05.107 --> 34:06.052
That's a joke !

34:07.636 --> 34:09.027
Since I just got promoted,

34:09.110 --> 34:12.014
I just thought you two should know that
I take my coffee with a little milk,

34:12.110 --> 34:14.722
two sugars and a lot
less of your bullshit.

34:16.223 --> 34:18.460
- I hate her.
- What a bitch!

34:18.588 --> 34:20.722
Don't even turn to see the wreckage.

34:25.914 --> 34:27.804
Can you describe the other kid ?

34:31.725 --> 34:33.032
What the hell ?

34:34.315 --> 34:37.087
The other kid was a little
taller than this one.

34:37.183 --> 34:38.803
Slender built, baggy jeans.

34:39.135 --> 34:42.795
He had on a black sweatshirt with
some gang gang bull on the back of it.

34:42.871 --> 34:46.168
And then he headed North.

34:46.744 --> 34:48.813
He was pretty banged up to.

34:49.516 --> 34:50.571
What's your name ?

34:50.998 --> 34:51.906
Roxy.

34:52.842 --> 34:54.741
You're the one who close on this kid ?

34:55.943 --> 34:57.479
I like your style.

34:58.903 --> 35:00.008
You got the wrong job, Roxy.

35:01.227 --> 35:03.429
I ain't got nothing but wrong jobs.

35:05.242 --> 35:08.626
So do you guys just, like,
hate each other's guts ?

35:08.856 --> 35:11.222
No, your mother and I
don't hate each other.

35:11.913 --> 35:13.223
We love each other very much.

35:14.011 --> 35:17.412
- We just...
- We just can't live together.

35:18.364 --> 35:19.962
But we both love you.

35:21.026 --> 35:23.393
And even though others things

35:24.221 --> 35:25.895
will change, that won't.

35:26.132 --> 35:29.352
You know, Regg', it's okay to
feel whatever you're feeling.

35:30.039 --> 35:32.522
Don't be afraid to have feelings.

35:34.821 --> 35:36.618
What are your feelings, sweetheart ?

35:37.319 --> 35:38.503
I'm a little hungry.

35:40.909 --> 35:42.926
So which one of you gets...

35:43.161 --> 35:46.642
Well, your mother and I haven't
exactly worked that out but

35:47.098 --> 35:48.757
I know your mom wants you to...

35:48.900 --> 35:49.827
Who gets JD ?

35:52.157 --> 35:53.068
Well, sweetheart,

35:53.267 --> 35:54.548
JD is your dog.

35:54.998 --> 35:56.448
But I'm sure if you wanna

35:57.462 --> 35:58.930
lend him to your dad

35:59.335 --> 36:00.744
every now and then, you know.

36:01.588 --> 36:03.022
I'm sure he'd appreciate it.

36:03.395 --> 36:05.141
Titia Carter's parents got a divorce

36:05.433 --> 36:08.086
and her dad got this
really cheesy condo.

36:08.234 --> 36:10.661
Shag carpeting and mirrors everywhere.

36:10.845 --> 36:12.806
Well, I'm not gonna get
a cheesy condo, Reggie.

36:13.080 --> 36:14.343
You have to get a backyard.

36:14.807 --> 36:15.792
For JD.

36:16.278 --> 36:17.256
We'll see, sweetie.

36:17.462 --> 36:19.646
Most sorority houses
do come with backyards.

36:19.721 --> 36:21.151
You just can't leave it alone.

36:21.234 --> 36:22.602
You just can't help yourself.

36:22.832 --> 36:25.920
Great! I can't help myself.

36:26.057 --> 36:31.191
You've been tapping little Mrs. Kappa
Kappa Gamma's keg for a year now.

36:31.606 --> 36:33.835
Did it ever occur to you that maybe

36:33.902 --> 36:35.396
you pushed me in that direction ?

36:35.739 --> 36:39.985
Oh really! Poor you!
Please enlighten me!

36:40.076 --> 36:42.508
That's the way that you drive
everyone around you away.

36:42.723 --> 36:44.500
You did the same thing to George.

36:44.623 --> 36:46.041
You wanted her out of this house.

36:46.166 --> 36:48.565
You wanted her gone and now she's gone.

36:49.738 --> 36:50.812
Get out.

36:51.064 --> 36:52.064
Get out!

36:52.790 --> 36:56.557
Get out of this house
right now or I will scream!

37:01.279 --> 37:04.745
My parents took me and my little
sister to the circus every year.

37:05.129 --> 37:07.197
I like the trapeze artists the best.

37:07.274 --> 37:10.022
The flying Wallendas or
whatever they were called.

37:10.173 --> 37:11.937
Not the death defying stuff,

37:12.010 --> 37:15.138
the midair quadruple
flips and near misses.

37:15.528 --> 37:17.125
I covered my eyes for that.

37:17.202 --> 37:19.014
What I liked was part of the end,

37:19.108 --> 37:22.967
when they bounce into the net and
jumped up with that big Wallenda smile.

37:23.166 --> 37:24.646
The "tada!" part.

37:25.189 --> 37:26.107
Tada!

37:26.285 --> 37:27.303
I love that.

37:27.499 --> 37:29.050
It meant "I'm safe".

37:30.576 --> 37:31.546
Hi!

37:32.217 --> 37:33.211
Hi.

37:37.471 --> 37:39.090
I can't go out with you tonight.

37:39.601 --> 37:40.506
Okay.

37:41.830 --> 37:43.268
Maybe some other time.

37:44.440 --> 37:47.210
I don't... I don't know.

37:48.735 --> 37:49.692
Okay.

37:50.765 --> 37:52.414
That's cool, you know.

37:52.520 --> 37:55.174
Just... hang on to my phone number.

37:57.261 --> 37:58.208
Okay.

37:58.296 --> 37:59.827
Hopefully, I'll see around some time.

38:01.091 --> 38:04.547
Well, we work in the same office.

38:04.937 --> 38:05.890
Yeah.

38:09.403 --> 38:10.415
Does it hurt ?

38:12.160 --> 38:13.194
Your finger...

38:14.910 --> 38:15.891
No.

38:16.322 --> 38:17.516
Good. Good, I'm glad.

38:20.568 --> 38:21.518
Thank you.

38:32.060 --> 38:33.094
Tada!

38:33.490 --> 38:35.555
That was the thing with the Wallendas.

38:35.763 --> 38:38.570
Why I always covered my
eyes until it was over.

38:38.891 --> 38:41.069
Eventually one of them's gotta fall.

38:49.753 --> 38:51.170
Daddy, it's not breaking!

38:51.389 --> 38:52.724
I know, sweetheart.

38:59.470 --> 39:02.425
Hey, Eddy. Finish this.

39:06.388 --> 39:07.518
Oh man!

39:09.250 --> 39:10.786
Try not to kill anyone.

39:20.008 --> 39:23.570
Daddy! Daddy! It's still not breaking!

39:23.841 --> 39:24.743
Sweetie...

39:25.291 --> 39:28.034
The piñata is gonna crack
open. You'll get your candy.

39:30.512 --> 39:32.351
Has daddy ever let you down before ?

39:32.710 --> 39:34.537
- No.
- No...

39:45.168 --> 39:46.672
I'll bring it right back.

39:49.534 --> 39:50.491
Knock it out.

40:24.068 --> 40:26.515
- Am I dead?
- Yeah.

40:27.141 --> 40:28.078
Yeah, you're dead.

40:29.397 --> 40:30.351
Who are you ?

40:30.595 --> 40:32.157
Ma.. Mason.

40:35.964 --> 40:37.063
You're not the clown ?

40:37.170 --> 40:39.238
I'm no fucking clown.

40:39.320 --> 40:40.693
What were you doing here ?

40:41.041 --> 40:44.768
I was... I took your soul
before you, you know...

40:44.821 --> 40:46.847
And now I'm supposed to
escort you to your lights.

40:46.914 --> 40:49.142
No, what were you doing ?

40:49.992 --> 40:52.623
You made obscene balloon
animals for my daughter.

40:53.057 --> 40:54.841
You insulted all my guests.

40:55.455 --> 40:57.543
And the whole time you
knew I was gonna die.

40:58.198 --> 40:59.591
This is a joke ?

41:06.253 --> 41:08.541
This is how she'll
remember her birthday ?

41:08.625 --> 41:11.147
Do you wanna come with me ? I'll
take you to your lights, alright ?

41:11.250 --> 41:12.371
Stay away from me!

41:13.374 --> 41:15.161
Stay away from my family!

41:15.483 --> 41:17.301
Just.. just go!

41:46.022 --> 41:48.781
Life always seemed to
be about two things:

41:49.180 --> 41:51.088
feeling bad and then feeling better.

41:52.122 --> 41:55.020
For me, the feeling bad
part came pretty easy.

41:56.864 --> 41:58.175
But the feeling better part,

41:58.964 --> 42:00.637
how to make myself feel better,

42:01.795 --> 42:03.542
I never got that part down.

42:09.452 --> 42:11.069
These are too soft, always break.

42:11.119 --> 42:14.201
I keep telling you to buy the
number fours but you don't listen.

42:16.586 --> 42:17.627
What's with the sad face ?

42:18.174 --> 42:19.346
Some sad story.

42:19.465 --> 42:22.351
Rent's due, job sucks, cat's pregnant.

42:22.418 --> 42:24.474
You haven't seen Mason
lately, have you ?

42:25.873 --> 42:28.005
Tiffany, can I get some coffee please ?

42:28.173 --> 42:29.806
Why do you drink coffee so late ?

42:30.768 --> 42:32.111
You don't sleep as it is.

42:32.520 --> 42:33.938
Make that an espresso.

42:34.282 --> 42:35.296
Thank you.

42:35.751 --> 42:37.763
Little Mrs. Cranky Pants

42:38.076 --> 42:39.878
Whatever haunts your
soul at this moment,

42:42.420 --> 42:45.694
whatever need you feel to make
some kind of a statement or

42:46.313 --> 42:47.850
question my authority and...

42:51.628 --> 42:52.852
Is it something I did ?

42:53.036 --> 42:53.952
Nothing's wrong.

42:56.421 --> 42:57.987
I got a promotion.

42:58.078 --> 42:59.706
What kind of promotion did you get ?

42:59.774 --> 43:02.421
Two more big bills a week.

43:02.979 --> 43:04.537
I joined the police academy.

43:04.669 --> 43:05.635
No, you didn't.

43:05.913 --> 43:06.844
Yes, she did.

43:07.357 --> 43:09.831
They want more days
these Happy Time people.

43:11.479 --> 43:13.337
I think you should decline the offer.

43:13.424 --> 43:15.682
Fuck that! It's done. I'm doing it.

43:15.774 --> 43:17.275
Roxy, give us a moment, will you ?

43:20.255 --> 43:21.472
Why can't I do this ?

43:21.622 --> 43:24.453
I'm doing this. She's joining
the fucking police academy.

43:24.862 --> 43:26.327
Roxy's not you concern.

43:27.345 --> 43:29.537
I'm just worried that
you're taking on too much.

43:31.662 --> 43:34.636
People love to take roses and
they forget about the thorns.

43:34.955 --> 43:37.022
Okay, now that's really beautiful but

43:37.765 --> 43:39.045
I'm taking the promotion.

43:45.444 --> 43:47.038
I wouldn't do that.

43:48.318 --> 43:49.305
What did she do now ?

43:49.741 --> 43:50.837
Nice cross.

43:51.051 --> 43:52.630
Had any trouble getting the blood off ?

43:52.961 --> 43:54.006
No, just soap and water.

43:54.084 --> 43:55.926
I just think you should
go there tomorrow morning

43:56.008 --> 43:57.933
and tell that Dolores woman "thank you"

43:58.988 --> 43:59.979
but no.

44:00.539 --> 44:01.959
I want to do this.

44:02.562 --> 44:03.575
I want more money.

44:04.753 --> 44:06.504
I want, I want...

44:08.424 --> 44:10.698
- Look, peanut.
- Don't call me that.

44:16.939 --> 44:20.312
I just think all that want thing
is not so good at this point.

44:21.781 --> 44:24.224
That's all I have to
say about your promotion.

44:24.978 --> 44:28.541
Well, as mush as I've
enjoyed this little pow wow,

44:28.623 --> 44:31.548
I think I'm just going to
do what I'm going to do.

44:33.802 --> 44:35.775
Mrs.! Your espresso ?

44:36.051 --> 44:37.032
I don't want it.

44:37.110 --> 44:38.832
We made it. Somebody's gotta pay for it.

44:40.133 --> 44:43.077
She's a cop. Don't they
get everything for free ?

44:44.279 --> 44:45.929
I thought you were a meter maid.

44:46.637 --> 44:48.125
Well, I'm a cop now.

44:48.588 --> 44:49.789
Good for you, baby.

44:50.132 --> 44:51.683
Coffee's free for cops.

44:52.449 --> 44:54.443
Un-fucking-real!

44:59.220 --> 45:00.572
What do you mean "you're a cop" ?

45:00.962 --> 45:03.111
I joined the police
academy this afternoon.

45:05.088 --> 45:06.695
Yeah, I don't think I care for that.

46:40.008 --> 46:41.907
Hey there, Mr. Frog.

46:42.808 --> 46:43.865
How was your day ?

46:45.297 --> 46:47.478
Mine was fucked up.

47:00.526 --> 47:01.727
My flower.

47:09.689 --> 47:10.922
I thought you might want it.

47:14.200 --> 47:15.894
So who was that boy on the phone today ?

47:16.253 --> 47:17.208
Brendan.

47:17.974 --> 47:20.252
- Brennan.
- Brennan.

47:21.001 --> 47:24.036
Who's Brennan who thinks
you have beautiful eyes ?

47:24.158 --> 47:25.341
Nobody.

47:27.302 --> 47:29.507
- Okay, I kissed him!
- And ?

47:29.714 --> 47:31.880
- And ?
- What was the kiss like ?

47:34.455 --> 47:37.148
It's not too late to call him, you know.

47:37.214 --> 47:38.138
I'm not gonna call him.

47:38.182 --> 47:41.632
Dolores doesn't want me getting
involved with anyone at Happy Time.

47:41.798 --> 47:42.902
Besides he's not my type.

47:43.236 --> 47:44.142
Not even close.

47:44.602 --> 47:45.588
He's a pretty boy.

47:46.144 --> 47:47.215
It's obvious.

47:48.166 --> 47:49.272
Go to bed, Daisy.

47:51.970 --> 47:53.767
So Rube doesn't want you at Happy time.

47:53.905 --> 47:55.048
That makes you unhappy.

47:55.139 --> 47:58.616
Dolores wants you at Happy Time
but just so long as you're unhappy.

47:58.703 --> 47:59.923
It just... sounds like a plan.

48:01.467 --> 48:03.117
Life sucks and then you die.

48:03.726 --> 48:06.168
And then it still sucks.

48:08.697 --> 48:09.825
What's with the cross ?

48:11.252 --> 48:12.293
I don't know I like it.

48:12.604 --> 48:14.216
What are you like catholic now ?

48:14.892 --> 48:16.013
Yeah. Why not ?

48:16.215 --> 48:17.181
Good for you!

48:19.117 --> 48:20.898
- You're so angry.
- And you're not ?

48:20.975 --> 48:21.955
Listen to me,

48:23.905 --> 48:25.733
I died in 1938

48:25.967 --> 48:29.141
and there is not a day that goes by
that I don't wonder the things I did,

48:29.449 --> 48:30.472
things I didn't do.

48:30.539 --> 48:34.169
I know and you were going
to a great actress and

48:34.430 --> 48:36.208
you're beautiful and talented

48:36.295 --> 48:38.598
and you slept with all
the men under the moon.

48:38.685 --> 48:40.872
Stop making fun of me.
Just shut up for once.

48:41.031 --> 48:43.628
You think you know everything
? Look how unhappy you are!

48:46.078 --> 48:49.038
I'm sorry you were so young
when you died, Georgia.

48:51.736 --> 48:52.758
Good night.

49:01.131 --> 49:03.288
I knew who that pink flower was for.

49:04.316 --> 49:06.027
I knew who I betrayed.

49:07.092 --> 49:10.670
My short life was like our
family outings to the circus.

49:11.372 --> 49:12.642
It wasn't so bad.

49:13.727 --> 49:16.226
A bit with a clown, some cotton candy...

49:18.038 --> 49:19.943
And just as things got interesting,

49:21.004 --> 49:22.390
I covered my eyes.

49:25.934 --> 49:28.811
I know what that Wallenda
smile at the end was about,

49:30.941 --> 49:34.689
why they were so happy with their
midair flips and near misses.

49:35.606 --> 49:39.107
They were happy because they were
brave enough to be themselves.

49:41.079 --> 49:42.580
I mean if you're a Wallenda,

49:43.316 --> 49:45.097
you have to climb up that ladder,

49:46.471 --> 49:48.569
you have to grab that trapeze bar.

49:50.740 --> 49:51.913
If you're a Wallenda,

49:53.525 --> 49:54.949
you have to jump off...

49:56.142 --> 49:57.848
eyes wide open.

